Abelgas Zirk’s Reflection:
I focused primarily on the technical architecture and the backend development of the FZ A-Tracker. I was responsible for coding the entire Flask application, which involved creating the routes for each CRUD operation and ensuring that the JSON-based database could handle data persistence without errors. A significant portion of his effort went into the mathematical logic of the system, specifically implementing the weighted linear regression algorithm that calculates performance trends and the dynamic formula that determines a student's standing based on customizable weights.

